20// setup this core backend
21bool NavEKF3_core::setup_core(uint8_t _imu_index, uint8_t _core_index)
22{
23 imu_index = _imu_index;
24 gyro_index_active = imu_index;
25 accel_index_active = imu_index;
26 core_index = _core_index;
27
28 /*
29 The imu_buffer_length needs to cope with the worst case sensor delay at the
30 target EKF state prediction rate. Non-IMU data coming in faster is downsampled.
31 */
32
33 // Calculate the expected EKF time step
34 if (dal.ins().get_loop_rate_hz() > 0) {
35 dtEkfAvg = 1.0f / dal.ins().get_loop_rate_hz();
36 dtEkfAvg = MAX(dtEkfAvg,EKF_TARGET_DT);
37 } else {
38 return false;
39 }
40
41 // find the maximum time delay for all potential sensors
42 uint16_t maxTimeDelay_ms = MAX(frontend->_hgtDelay_ms ,
43 MAX(frontend->_flowDelay_ms ,
44 MAX(frontend->_rngBcnDelay_ms ,
45 MAX(frontend->magDelay_ms ,
46 (uint16_t)(EKF_TARGET_DT_MS)
47 ))));
48
49 // GPS sensing can have large delays and should not be included if disabled
50 if (frontend->sources.usingGPS()) {
51 // Wait for the configuration of all GPS units to be confirmed. Until this has occurred the GPS driver cannot provide a correct time delay
52 float gps_delay_sec = 0;
53 if (!dal.gps().get_lag(selected_gps, gps_delay_sec)) {
54#if HAL_GCS_ENABLED
55 const uint32_t now = dal.millis();
56 if (now - lastInitFailReport_ms > 10000) {
57 lastInitFailReport_ms = now;
58 // provide an escalating series of messages
59 MAV_SEVERITY severity = MAV_SEVERITY_INFO;
60 if (now > 30000) {
61 severity = MAV_SEVERITY_ERROR;
62 } else if (now > 15000) {
63 severity = MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING;
64 }
65 GCS_SEND_TEXT(severity, "EKF3 waiting for GPS config data");
66 }
67#endif
68 return false;
69 }
70 // limit the time delay value from the GPS library to a max of 250 msec which is the max value the EKF has been tested for.
71 maxTimeDelay_ms = MAX(maxTimeDelay_ms , MIN((uint16_t)(gps_delay_sec * 1000.0f),250));
72 }
73
74 // airspeed sensing can have large delays and should not be included if disabled
75 if (dal.airspeed_sensor_enabled()) {
76 maxTimeDelay_ms = MAX(maxTimeDelay_ms , frontend->tasDelay_ms);
77 }
78
79#if HAL_VISUALODOM_ENABLED
80 // include delay from visual odometry if enabled
81 const auto *visual_odom = dal.visualodom();
82 if ((visual_odom != nullptr) && visual_odom->enabled()) {
83 maxTimeDelay_ms = MAX(maxTimeDelay_ms, MIN(visual_odom->get_delay_ms(), 250));
84 }
85#endif
86
87 // calculate the IMU buffer length required to accommodate the maximum delay with some allowance for jitter
88 imu_buffer_length = (maxTimeDelay_ms / (uint16_t)(EKF_TARGET_DT_MS)) + 1;
89
90 // set the observation buffer length to handle the minimum time of arrival between observations in combination
91 // with the worst case delay from current time to ekf fusion time
92 // allow for worst case 50% extension of the ekf fusion time horizon delay due to timing jitter
93 uint16_t ekf_delay_ms = maxTimeDelay_ms + (int)(ceilF((ftype)maxTimeDelay_ms * 0.5f));
94 obs_buffer_length = (ekf_delay_ms / frontend->sensorIntervalMin_ms) + 1;
95
96 // limit to be no longer than the IMU buffer (we can't process data faster than the EKF prediction rate)
97 obs_buffer_length = MIN(obs_buffer_length,imu_buffer_length);
98
99 // calculate buffer size for optical flow data
100 const uint8_t flow_buffer_length = MIN((ekf_delay_ms / frontend->flowIntervalMin_ms) + 1, imu_buffer_length);
101
102#if EK3_FEATURE_EXTERNAL_NAV
103 // calculate buffer size for external nav data
104 const uint8_t extnav_buffer_length = MIN((ekf_delay_ms / frontend->extNavIntervalMin_ms) + 1, imu_buffer_length);
105#endif // EK3_FEATURE_EXTERNAL_NAV
106
107 if(!storedGPS.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
108 return false;
109 }
110 if(!storedMag.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
111 return false;
112 }
113 if(!storedBaro.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
114 return false;
115 }
116 if(dal.airspeed() && !storedTAS.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
117 return false;
118 }
119 if(dal.opticalflow_enabled() && !storedOF.init(flow_buffer_length)) {
120 return false;
121 }
122#if EK3_FEATURE_BODY_ODOM
123 if(frontend->sources.ext_nav_enabled() && !storedBodyOdm.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
124 return false;
125 }
126 if(frontend->sources.wheel_encoder_enabled() && !storedWheelOdm.init(imu_buffer_length)) {
127 // initialise to same length of IMU to allow for multiple wheel sensors
128 return false;
129 }
130#endif // EK3_FEATURE_BODY_ODOM
131 if(frontend->sources.gps_yaw_enabled() && !storedYawAng.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
132 return false;
133 }
134 // Note: the use of dual range finders potentially doubles the amount of data to be stored
135 if(dal.rangefinder() && !storedRange.init(MIN(2*obs_buffer_length , imu_buffer_length))) {
136 return false;
137 }
138 // Note: range beacon data is read one beacon at a time and can arrive at a high rate
139#if EK3_FEATURE_BEACON_FUSION
140 if(dal.beacon() && !rngBcn.storedRange.init(imu_buffer_length+1)) {
141 return false;
142 }
143#endif
144#if EK3_FEATURE_EXTERNAL_NAV
145 if (frontend->sources.ext_nav_enabled() && !storedExtNav.init(extnav_buffer_length)) {
146 return false;
147 }
148 if (frontend->sources.ext_nav_enabled() && !storedExtNavVel.init(extnav_buffer_length)) {
149 return false;
150 }
151 if(frontend->sources.ext_nav_enabled() && !storedExtNavYawAng.init(extnav_buffer_length)) {
152 return false;
153 }
154#endif // EK3_FEATURE_EXTERNAL_NAV
155 if(!storedIMU.init(imu_buffer_length)) {
156 return false;
157 }
158 if(!storedOutput.init(imu_buffer_length)) {
159 return false;
160 }
161#if EK3_FEATURE_DRAG_FUSION
162 if (!storedDrag.init(obs_buffer_length)) {
163 return false;
164 }
165#endif
166
167 if ((yawEstimator == nullptr) && (frontend->_gsfRunMask & (1U<<core_index))) {
168 // check if there is enough memory to create the EKF-GSF object
169 if (dal.available_memory() < sizeof(EKFGSF_yaw) + 1024) {
170 GCS_SEND_TEXT(MAV_SEVERITY_CRITICAL, "EKF3 IMU%u GSF: not enough memory",(unsigned)imu_index);
171 return false;
172 }
173
174 // try to instantiate
175 yawEstimator = new EKFGSF_yaw();
176 if (yawEstimator == nullptr) {
177 GCS_SEND_TEXT(MAV_SEVERITY_CRITICAL, "EKF3 IMU%uGSF: allocation failed",(unsigned)imu_index);
178 return false;
179 }
180 }
181
182 return true;
183}

446/*
447Initialise the states from accelerometer data. This assumes measured acceleration
448is dominated by gravity. If this assumption is not true then the EKF will require
449timee to reduce the resulting tilt error. Yaw alignment is not performed by this
450function, but is perfomred later and initiated the SelectMagFusion() function
451after the tilt has stabilised.
452*/
453
454bool NavEKF3_core::InitialiseFilterBootstrap(void)
455{
456 // update sensor selection (for affinity)
457 update_sensor_selection();
458
459 // If we are a plane and don't have GPS lock then don't initialise
460 if (assume_zero_sideslip() && dal.gps().status(preferred_gps) < AP_DAL_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
461 dal.snprintf(prearm_fail_string,
462 sizeof(prearm_fail_string),
463 "EKF3 init failure: No GPS lock");
464 statesInitialised = false;
465 return false;
466 }
467
468 // read all the sensors required to start the EKF the states
469 readIMUData();
470 readMagData();
471 readGpsData();
472 readGpsYawData();
473 readBaroData();
474
475 if (statesInitialised) {
476 // we are initialised, but we don't return true until the IMU
477 // buffer has been filled. This prevents a timing
478 // vulnerability with a pause in IMU data during filter startup
479 return storedIMU.is_filled();
480 }
481
482 // accumulate enough sensor data to fill the buffers
483 if (firstInitTime_ms == 0) {
484 firstInitTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
485 return false;
486 } else if (imuSampleTime_ms - firstInitTime_ms < 1000) {
487 return false;
488 }
489
490 // set re-used variables to zero
491 InitialiseVariables();
492
493 // acceleration vector in XYZ body axes measured by the IMU (m/s^2)
494 Vector3F initAccVec;
495
496 // TODO we should average accel readings over several cycles
497 initAccVec = dal.ins().get_accel(accel_index_active).toftype();
498
499 // normalise the acceleration vector
500 ftype pitch=0, roll=0;
501 if (initAccVec.length() > 0.001f) {
502 initAccVec.normalize();
503
504 // calculate initial pitch angle
505 pitch = asinF(initAccVec.x);
506
507 // calculate initial roll angle
508 roll = atan2F(-initAccVec.y , -initAccVec.z);
509 }
510
511 // calculate initial roll and pitch orientation
512 stateStruct.quat.from_euler(roll, pitch, 0.0f);
513
514 // initialise dynamic states
515 stateStruct.velocity.zero();
516 stateStruct.position.zero();
517
518 // initialise static process model states
519 stateStruct.gyro_bias.zero();
520 stateStruct.accel_bias.zero();
521 stateStruct.wind_vel.zero();
522 stateStruct.earth_magfield.zero();
523 stateStruct.body_magfield.zero();
524
525 // set the position, velocity and height
526 ResetVelocity(resetDataSource::DEFAULT);
527 ResetPosition(resetDataSource::DEFAULT);
528 ResetHeight();
529
530 // initialise sources
531 posxy_source_last = frontend->sources.getPosXYSource();
532 yaw_source_last = frontend->sources.getYawSource();
533
534 // define Earth rotation vector in the NED navigation frame
535 calcEarthRateNED(earthRateNED, dal.get_home().lat);
536
537 // initialise the covariance matrix
538 CovarianceInit();
539
540 // reset the output predictor states
541 StoreOutputReset();
542
543 // set to true now that states have be initialised
544 statesInitialised = true;
545
546 // reset inactive biases
547 for (uint8_t i=0; i<INS_MAX_INSTANCES; i++) {
548 inactiveBias[i].gyro_bias.zero();
549 inactiveBias[i].accel_bias.zero();
550 }
551
552 GCS_SEND_TEXT(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "EKF3 IMU%u initialised",(unsigned)imu_index);
553
554 // we initially return false to wait for the IMU buffer to fill
555 return false;
556}
557
558// initialise the covariance matrix
559void NavEKF3_core::CovarianceInit()
560{
561 // zero the matrix
562 memset(&P[0][0], 0, sizeof(P));
563
564 // define the initial angle uncertainty as variances for a rotation vector
565 Vector3F rot_vec_var;
566 rot_vec_var.x = rot_vec_var.y = rot_vec_var.z = sq(0.1f);
567
568 // reset the quaternion state covariances
569 CovariancePrediction(&rot_vec_var);
570
571 // velocities
572 P[4][4] = sq(frontend->_gpsHorizVelNoise);
573 P[5][5] = P[4][4];
574 P[6][6] = sq(frontend->_gpsVertVelNoise);
575 // positions
576 P[7][7] = sq(frontend->_gpsHorizPosNoise);
577 P[8][8] = P[7][7];
578 P[9][9] = sq(frontend->_baroAltNoise);
579 // gyro delta angle biases
580 P[10][10] = sq(radians(InitialGyroBiasUncertainty() * dtEkfAvg));
581 P[11][11] = P[10][10];
582 P[12][12] = P[10][10];
583 // delta velocity biases
584 P[13][13] = sq(ACCEL_BIAS_LIM_SCALER * frontend->_accBiasLim * dtEkfAvg);
585 P[14][14] = P[13][13];
586 P[15][15] = P[13][13];
587 // earth magnetic field
588 P[16][16] = sq(frontend->_magNoise);
589 P[17][17] = P[16][16];
590 P[18][18] = P[16][16];
591 // body magnetic field
592 P[19][19] = sq(frontend->_magNoise);
593 P[20][20] = P[19][19];
594 P[21][21] = P[19][19];
595 // wind velocities
596 P[22][22] = 0.0f;
597 P[23][23] = P[22][22];
598
599
600 // optical flow ground height covariance
601 Popt = 0.25f;
602
603}

605/********************************************************
606* UPDATE FUNCTIONS *
607********************************************************/
608// Update Filter States - this should be called whenever new IMU data is available
609void NavEKF3_core::UpdateFilter(bool predict)
610{
611 // Set the flag to indicate to the filter that the front-end has given permission for a new state prediction cycle to be started
612 startPredictEnabled = predict;
613
614 // don't run filter updates if states have not been initialised
615 if (!statesInitialised) {
616 return;
617 }
618
619 fill_scratch_variables();
620
621 // update sensor selection (for affinity)
622 update_sensor_selection();
623
624 // TODO - in-flight restart method
625
626 // Check arm status and perform required checks and mode changes
627 controlFilterModes();
628
629 // read IMU data as delta angles and velocities
630 readIMUData();
631
632 // Run the EKF equations to estimate at the fusion time horizon if new IMU data is available in the buffer
633 if (runUpdates) {
634 // Predict states using IMU data from the delayed time horizon
635 UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED();
636
637 // Predict the covariance growth
638 CovariancePrediction(nullptr);
639
640 // Run the IMU prediction step for the GSF yaw estimator algorithm
641 // using IMU and optionally true airspeed data.
642 // Must be run before SelectMagFusion() to provide an up to date yaw estimate
643 runYawEstimatorPrediction();
644
645 // Update states using magnetometer or external yaw sensor data
646 SelectMagFusion();
647
648 // Update states using GPS and altimeter data
649 SelectVelPosFusion();
650
651 // Run the GPS velocity correction step for the GSF yaw estimator algorithm
652 // and use the yaw estimate to reset the main EKF yaw if requested
653 // Muat be run after SelectVelPosFusion() so that fresh GPS data is available
654 runYawEstimatorCorrection();
655
656#if EK3_FEATURE_BEACON_FUSION
657 // Update states using range beacon data
658 SelectRngBcnFusion();
659#endif
660
661 // Update states using optical flow data
662 SelectFlowFusion();
663
664#if EK3_FEATURE_BODY_ODOM
665 // Update states using body frame odometry data
666 SelectBodyOdomFusion();
667#endif
668
669 // Update states using airspeed data
670 SelectTasFusion();
671
672 // Update states using sideslip constraint assumption for fly-forward vehicles or body drag for multicopters
673 SelectBetaDragFusion();
674
675 // Update the filter status
676 updateFilterStatus();
677
678 if (imuSampleTime_ms - last_oneHz_ms >= 1000) {
679 // 1Hz tasks
680 last_oneHz_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
681 moveEKFOrigin();
682 checkUpdateEarthField();
683 }
684 }
685
686 // Wind output forward from the fusion to output time horizon
687 calcOutputStates();
688
689 /*
690 this is a check to cope with a vehicle sitting idle on the
691 ground and getting over-confident of the state. The symptoms
692 would be "gyros still settling" when the user tries to arm. In
693 that state the EKF can't recover, so we do a hard reset and let
694 it try again.
695 */
696 if (filterStatus.value != 0) {
697 last_filter_ok_ms = dal.millis();
698 }
699 if (filterStatus.value == 0 &&
700 last_filter_ok_ms != 0 &&
701 dal.millis() - last_filter_ok_ms > 5000 &&
702 !dal.get_armed()) {
703 // we've been unhealthy for 5 seconds after being healthy, reset the filter
704 GCS_SEND_TEXT(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING, "EKF3 IMU%u forced reset",(unsigned)imu_index);
705 last_filter_ok_ms = 0;
706 statesInitialised = false;
707 InitialiseFilterBootstrap();
708 }
709}
710
711void NavEKF3_core::correctDeltaAngle(Vector3F &delAng, ftype delAngDT, uint8_t gyro_index)
712{
713 delAng -= inactiveBias[gyro_index].gyro_bias * (delAngDT / dtEkfAvg);
714}
715
716void NavEKF3_core::correctDeltaVelocity(Vector3F &delVel, ftype delVelDT, uint8_t accel_index)
717{
718 delVel -= inactiveBias[accel_index].accel_bias * (delVelDT / dtEkfAvg);
719}
720
721/*
722 * Update the quaternion, velocity and position states using delayed IMU measurements
723 * because the EKF is running on a delayed time horizon. Note that the quaternion is
724 * not used by the EKF equations, which instead estimate the error in the attitude of
725 * the vehicle when each observation is fused. This attitude error is then used to correct
726 * the quaternion.
727*/
728void NavEKF3_core::UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED()
729{
730 // update the quaternion states by rotating from the previous attitude through
731 // the delta angle rotation quaternion and normalise
732 // apply correction for earth's rotation rate
733 // % * - and + operators have been overloaded
734 stateStruct.quat.rotate(delAngCorrected - prevTnb * earthRateNED*imuDataDelayed.delAngDT);
735
736 stateStruct.quat.normalize();
737
738 // transform body delta velocities to delta velocities in the nav frame
739 // use the nav frame from previous time step as the delta velocities
740 // have been rotated into that frame
741 // * and + operators have been overloaded
742 Vector3F delVelNav; // delta velocity vector in earth axes
743 delVelNav = prevTnb.mul_transpose(delVelCorrected);
744 delVelNav.z += GRAVITY_MSS*imuDataDelayed.delVelDT;
745
746 // calculate the nav to body cosine matrix
747 stateStruct.quat.inverse().rotation_matrix(prevTnb);
748
749 // calculate the rate of change of velocity (used for launch detect and other functions)
750 velDotNED = delVelNav / imuDataDelayed.delVelDT;
751
752 // apply a first order lowpass filter
753 velDotNEDfilt = velDotNED * 0.05f + velDotNEDfilt * 0.95f;
754
755 // calculate a magnitude of the filtered nav acceleration (required for GPS
756 // variance estimation)
757 accNavMag = velDotNEDfilt.length();
758 accNavMagHoriz = velDotNEDfilt.xy().length();
759
760 // if we are not aiding, then limit the horizontal magnitude of acceleration
761 // to prevent large manoeuvre transients disturbing the attitude
762 if ((PV_AidingMode == AID_NONE) && (accNavMagHoriz > 5.0f)) {
763 ftype gain = 5.0f/accNavMagHoriz;
764 delVelNav.x *= gain;
765 delVelNav.y *= gain;
766 }
767
768 // save velocity for use in trapezoidal integration for position calcuation
769 Vector3F lastVelocity = stateStruct.velocity;
770
771 // sum delta velocities to get velocity
772 stateStruct.velocity += delVelNav;
773
774 // apply a trapezoidal integration to velocities to calculate position
775 stateStruct.position += (stateStruct.velocity + lastVelocity) * (imuDataDelayed.delVelDT*0.5f);
776
777 // accumulate the bias delta angle and time since last reset by an OF measurement arrival
778 delAngBodyOF += delAngCorrected;
779 delTimeOF += imuDataDelayed.delAngDT;
780
781 // limit states to protect against divergence
782 ConstrainStates();
783
784#if EK3_FEATURE_BEACON_FUSION
785 // If main filter velocity states are valid, update the range beacon receiver position states
786 if (filterStatus.flags.horiz_vel) {
787 rngBcn.receiverPos += (stateStruct.velocity + lastVelocity) * (imuDataDelayed.delVelDT*0.5f);
788 }
789#endif
790}
791
792/*
793 * Propagate PVA solution forward from the fusion time horizon to the current time horizon
794 * using simple observer which performs two functions:
795 * 1) Corrects for the delayed time horizon used by the EKF.
796 * 2) Applies a LPF to state corrections to prevent 'stepping' in states due to measurement
797 * fusion introducing unwanted noise into the control loops.
798 * The inspiration for using a complementary filter to correct for time delays in the EKF
799 * is based on the work by A Khosravian.
800 *
801 * "Recursive Attitude Estimation in the Presence of Multi-rate and Multi-delay Vector Measurements"
802 * A Khosravian, J Trumpf, R Mahony, T Hamel, Australian National University
803*/
804void NavEKF3_core::calcOutputStates()
805{
806 // apply corrections to the IMU data
807 Vector3F delAngNewCorrected = imuDataNew.delAng;
808 Vector3F delVelNewCorrected = imuDataNew.delVel;
809 correctDeltaAngle(delAngNewCorrected, imuDataNew.delAngDT, imuDataNew.gyro_index);
810 correctDeltaVelocity(delVelNewCorrected, imuDataNew.delVelDT, imuDataNew.accel_index);
811
812 // apply corrections to track EKF solution
813 Vector3F delAng = delAngNewCorrected + delAngCorrection;
814
815 // convert the rotation vector to its equivalent quaternion
816 QuaternionF deltaQuat;
817 deltaQuat.from_axis_angle(delAng);
818
819 // update the quaternion states by rotating from the previous attitude through
820 // the delta angle rotation quaternion and normalise
821 outputDataNew.quat *= deltaQuat;
822 outputDataNew.quat.normalize();
823
824 // calculate the body to nav cosine matrix
825 Matrix3F Tbn_temp;
826 outputDataNew.quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn_temp);
827
828 // transform body delta velocities to delta velocities in the nav frame
829 Vector3F delVelNav = Tbn_temp*delVelNewCorrected;
830 delVelNav.z += GRAVITY_MSS*imuDataNew.delVelDT;
831
832 // save velocity for use in trapezoidal integration for position calcuation
833 Vector3F lastVelocity = outputDataNew.velocity;
834
835 // sum delta velocities to get velocity
836 outputDataNew.velocity += delVelNav;
837
838 // Implement third order complementary filter for height and height rate
839 // Reference Paper :
840 // Optimizing the Gains of the Baro-Inertial Vertical Channel
841 // Widnall W.S, Sinha P.K,
842 // AIAA Journal of Guidance and Control, 78-1307R
843
844 // Perform filter calculation using backwards Euler integration
845 // Coefficients selected to place all three filter poles at omega
846 const ftype CompFiltOmega = M_2PI * constrain_ftype(frontend->_hrt_filt_freq, 0.1f, 30.0f);
847 ftype omega2 = CompFiltOmega * CompFiltOmega;
848 ftype pos_err = constrain_ftype(outputDataNew.position.z - vertCompFiltState.pos, -1e5, 1e5);
849 ftype integ1_input = pos_err * omega2 * CompFiltOmega * imuDataNew.delVelDT;
850 vertCompFiltState.acc += integ1_input;
851 ftype integ2_input = delVelNav.z + (vertCompFiltState.acc + pos_err * omega2 * 3.0f) * imuDataNew.delVelDT;
852 vertCompFiltState.vel += integ2_input;
853 ftype integ3_input = (vertCompFiltState.vel + pos_err * CompFiltOmega * 3.0f) * imuDataNew.delVelDT;
854 vertCompFiltState.pos += integ3_input;
855
856 // apply a trapezoidal integration to velocities to calculate position
857 outputDataNew.position += (outputDataNew.velocity + lastVelocity) * (imuDataNew.delVelDT*0.5f);
858
859 // If the IMU accelerometer is offset from the body frame origin, then calculate corrections
860 // that can be added to the EKF velocity and position outputs so that they represent the velocity
861 // and position of the body frame origin.
862 // Note the * operator has been overloaded to operate as a dot product
863 if (!accelPosOffset.is_zero()) {
864 // calculate the average angular rate across the last IMU update
865 // note delAngDT is prevented from being zero in readIMUData()
866 Vector3F angRate = imuDataNew.delAng * (1.0f/imuDataNew.delAngDT);
867
868 // Calculate the velocity of the body frame origin relative to the IMU in body frame
869 // and rotate into earth frame. Note % operator has been overloaded to perform a cross product
870 Vector3F velBodyRelIMU = angRate % (- accelPosOffset);
871 velOffsetNED = Tbn_temp * velBodyRelIMU;
872
873 // calculate the earth frame position of the body frame origin relative to the IMU
874 posOffsetNED = Tbn_temp * (- accelPosOffset);
875 } else {
876 velOffsetNED.zero();
877 posOffsetNED.zero();
878 }
879
880 // Detect fixed wing launch acceleration using latest data from IMU to enable early startup of filter functions
881 // that use launch acceleration to detect start of flight
882 if (!inFlight && !dal.get_takeoff_expected() && assume_zero_sideslip()) {
883 const ftype launchDelVel = imuDataNew.delVel.x + GRAVITY_MSS * imuDataNew.delVelDT * Tbn_temp.c.x;
884 if (launchDelVel > GRAVITY_MSS * imuDataNew.delVelDT) {
885 dal.set_takeoff_expected();
886 }
887 }
888
889 // store INS states in a ring buffer that with the same length and time coordinates as the IMU data buffer
890 if (runUpdates) {
891 // store the states at the output time horizon
892 storedOutput[storedIMU.get_youngest_index()] = outputDataNew;
893
894 // recall the states from the fusion time horizon
895 outputDataDelayed = storedOutput[storedIMU.get_oldest_index()];
896
897 // compare quaternion data with EKF quaternion at the fusion time horizon and calculate correction
898
899 // divide the demanded quaternion by the estimated to get the error
900 QuaternionF quatErr = stateStruct.quat / outputDataDelayed.quat;
901
902 // Convert to a delta rotation using a small angle approximation
903 quatErr.normalize();
904 Vector3F deltaAngErr;
905 ftype scaler;
906 if (quatErr[0] >= 0.0f) {
907 scaler = 2.0f;
908 } else {
909 scaler = -2.0f;
910 }
911 deltaAngErr.x = scaler * quatErr[1];
912 deltaAngErr.y = scaler * quatErr[2];
913 deltaAngErr.z = scaler * quatErr[3];
914
915 // calculate a gain that provides tight tracking of the estimator states and
916 // adjust for changes in time delay to maintain consistent damping ratio of ~0.7
917 ftype timeDelay = 1e-3f * (ftype)(imuDataNew.time_ms - imuDataDelayed.time_ms);
918 timeDelay = MAX(timeDelay, dtIMUavg);
919 ftype errorGain = 0.5f / timeDelay;
920
921 // calculate a correction to the delta angle
922 // that will cause the INS to track the EKF quaternions
923 delAngCorrection = deltaAngErr * errorGain * dtIMUavg;
924
925 // calculate velocity and position tracking errors
926 Vector3F velErr = (stateStruct.velocity - outputDataDelayed.velocity);
927 Vector3F posErr = (stateStruct.position - outputDataDelayed.position);
928
929 if (badIMUdata) {
930 // When IMU accel is bad, calculate an integral that will be used to drive the difference
931 // between the output state and internal EKF state at the delayed time horizon to zero.
932 badImuVelErrIntegral += (stateStruct.velocity.z - outputDataNew.velocity.z);
933 } else {
934 badImuVelErrIntegral = velErrintegral.z;
935 }
936
937 // collect magnitude tracking error for diagnostics
938 outputTrackError.x = deltaAngErr.length();
939 outputTrackError.y = velErr.length();
940 outputTrackError.z = posErr.length();
941
942 // convert user specified time constant from centi-seconds to seconds
943 ftype tauPosVel = constrain_ftype(0.01f*(ftype)frontend->_tauVelPosOutput, 0.1f, 0.5f);
944
945 // calculate a gain to track the EKF position states with the specified time constant
946 ftype velPosGain = dtEkfAvg / constrain_ftype(tauPosVel, dtEkfAvg, 10.0f);
947
948 // use a PI feedback to calculate a correction that will be applied to the output state history
949 posErrintegral += posErr;
950 velErrintegral += velErr;
951 Vector3F posCorrection = posErr * velPosGain + posErrintegral * sq(velPosGain) * 0.1F;
952 Vector3F velCorrection;
953 velCorrection.x = velErr.x * velPosGain + velErrintegral.x * sq(velPosGain) * 0.1F;
954 velCorrection.y = velErr.y * velPosGain + velErrintegral.y * sq(velPosGain) * 0.1F;
955 if (badIMUdata) {
956 velCorrection.z = velErr.z * velPosGain + badImuVelErrIntegral * sq(velPosGain) * 0.07F;
957 velErrintegral.z = badImuVelErrIntegral;
958 } else {
959 velCorrection.z = velErr.z * velPosGain + velErrintegral.z * sq(velPosGain) * 0.1F;
960 }
961
962 // loop through the output filter state history and apply the corrections to the velocity and position states
963 // this method is too expensive to use for the attitude states due to the quaternion operations required
964 // but does not introduce a time delay in the 'correction loop' and allows smaller tracking time constants
965 // to be used
966 output_elements outputStates;
967 for (unsigned index=0; index < imu_buffer_length; index++) {
968 outputStates = storedOutput[index];
969
970 // a constant velocity correction is applied
971 outputStates.velocity += velCorrection;
972
973 // a constant position correction is applied
974 outputStates.position += posCorrection;
975
976 // push the updated data to the buffer
977 storedOutput[index] = outputStates;
978 }
979
980 // update output state to corrected values
981 outputDataNew = storedOutput[storedIMU.get_youngest_index()];
982
983 }
984}
985
986/*
987 * Calculate the predicted state covariance matrix using algebraic equations generated using SymPy
988 * See AP_NavEKF3/derivation/main.py for derivation
989 * Output for change reference: AP_NavEKF3/derivation/generated/covariance_generated.cpp
990 * Argument rotVarVecPtr is pointer to a vector defining the earth frame uncertainty variance of the quaternion states
991 * used to perform a reset of the quaternion state covariances only. Set to null for normal operation.
992*/
993void NavEKF3_core::CovariancePrediction(Vector3F *rotVarVecPtr)
994{
995 ftype daxVar; // X axis delta angle noise variance rad^2
996 ftype dayVar; // Y axis delta angle noise variance rad^2
997 ftype dazVar; // Z axis delta angle noise variance rad^2
998 ftype dvxVar; // X axis delta velocity variance noise (m/s)^2
999 ftype dvyVar; // Y axis delta velocity variance noise (m/s)^2
1000 ftype dvzVar; // Z axis delta velocity variance noise (m/s)^2
1001 ftype dvx; // X axis delta velocity (m/s)
1002 ftype dvy; // Y axis delta velocity (m/s)
1003 ftype dvz; // Z axis delta velocity (m/s)
1004 ftype dax; // X axis delta angle (rad)
1005 ftype day; // Y axis delta angle (rad)
1006 ftype daz; // Z axis delta angle (rad)
1007 ftype q0; // attitude quaternion
1008 ftype q1; // attitude quaternion
1009 ftype q2; // attitude quaternion
1010 ftype q3; // attitude quaternion
1011 ftype dax_b; // X axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1012 ftype day_b; // Y axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1013 ftype daz_b; // Z axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1014 ftype dvx_b; // X axis delta velocity measurement bias (rad)
1015 ftype dvy_b; // Y axis delta velocity measurement bias (rad)
1016 ftype dvz_b; // Z axis delta velocity measurement bias (rad)
1017
1018 // Calculate the time step used by the covariance prediction as an average of the gyro and accel integration period
1019 // Constrain to prevent bad timing jitter causing numerical conditioning problems with the covariance prediction
1020 dt = constrain_ftype(0.5f*(imuDataDelayed.delAngDT+imuDataDelayed.delVelDT),0.5f * dtEkfAvg, 2.0f * dtEkfAvg);
1021
1022 // use filtered height rate to increase wind process noise when climbing or descending
1023 // this allows for wind gradient effects.Filter height rate using a 10 second time constant filter
1024 ftype alpha = 0.1f * dt;
1025 hgtRate = hgtRate * (1.0f - alpha) - stateStruct.velocity.z * alpha;
1026
1027 // calculate covariance prediction process noise added to diagonals of predicted covariance matrix
1028 // error growth of first 10 kinematic states is built into auto-code for covariance prediction and driven by IMU noise parameters
1029 Vector14 processNoiseVariance = {};
1030
1031 if (!inhibitDelAngBiasStates) {
1032 ftype dAngBiasVar = sq(sq(dt) * constrain_ftype(frontend->_gyroBiasProcessNoise, 0.0, 1.0));
1033 for (uint8_t i=0; i<=2; i++) processNoiseVariance[i] = dAngBiasVar;
1034 }
1035
1036 if (!inhibitDelVelBiasStates) {
1037 // default process noise (m/s)^2
1038 ftype dVelBiasVar = sq(sq(dt) * constrain_ftype(frontend->_accelBiasProcessNoise, 0.0, 1.0));
1039 for (uint8_t i=3; i<=5; i++) {
1040 processNoiseVariance[i] = dVelBiasVar;
1041 }
1042 }
1043
1044 if (!inhibitMagStates && lastInhibitMagStates) {
1045 // when starting 3D fusion we want to reset mag variances
1046 needMagBodyVarReset = true;
1047 needEarthBodyVarReset = true;
1048 }
1049
1050 if (needMagBodyVarReset) {
1051 // reset body mag variances
1052 needMagBodyVarReset = false;
1053 zeroCols(P,19,21);
1054 zeroRows(P,19,21);
1055 P[19][19] = sq(frontend->_magNoise);
1056 P[20][20] = P[19][19];
1057 P[21][21] = P[19][19];
1058 }
1059
1060 if (needEarthBodyVarReset) {
1061 // reset mag earth field variances
1062 needEarthBodyVarReset = false;
1063 zeroCols(P,16,18);
1064 zeroRows(P,16,18);
1065 P[16][16] = sq(frontend->_magNoise);
1066 P[17][17] = P[16][16];
1067 P[18][18] = P[16][16];
1068 // Fusing the declinaton angle as an observaton with a 20 deg uncertainty helps
1069 // to stabilise the earth field.
1070 FuseDeclination(radians(20.0f));
1071 }
1072
1073 if (!inhibitMagStates) {
1074 ftype magEarthVar = sq(dt * constrain_ftype(frontend->_magEarthProcessNoise, 0.0f, 1.0f));
1075 ftype magBodyVar = sq(dt * constrain_ftype(frontend->_magBodyProcessNoise, 0.0f, 1.0f));
1076 for (uint8_t i=6; i<=8; i++) processNoiseVariance[i] = magEarthVar;
1077 for (uint8_t i=9; i<=11; i++) processNoiseVariance[i] = magBodyVar;
1078 }
1079 lastInhibitMagStates = inhibitMagStates;
1080
1081 if (!inhibitWindStates) {
1082 const bool isDragFusionDeadReckoning = filterStatus.flags.dead_reckoning && !dragTimeout;
1083 if (isDragFusionDeadReckoning) {
1084 // when dead reckoning using drag fusion stop learning wind states to provide a more stable velocity estimate
1085 P[23][23] = P[22][22] = 0.0f;
1086 } else {
1087 ftype windVelVar = sq(dt * constrain_ftype(frontend->_windVelProcessNoise, 0.0f, 1.0f) * (1.0f + constrain_ftype(frontend->_wndVarHgtRateScale, 0.0f, 1.0f) * fabsF(hgtRate)));
1088 if (!tasDataDelayed.allowFusion) {
1089 // Allow wind states to recover faster when using sideslip fusion with a failed airspeed sesnor
1090 windVelVar *= 10.0f;
1091 }
1092 for (uint8_t i=12; i<=13; i++) processNoiseVariance[i] = windVelVar;
1093 }
1094 }
1095
1096 // set variables used to calculate covariance growth
1097 dvx = imuDataDelayed.delVel.x;
1098 dvy = imuDataDelayed.delVel.y;
1099 dvz = imuDataDelayed.delVel.z;
1100 dax = imuDataDelayed.delAng.x;
1101 day = imuDataDelayed.delAng.y;
1102 daz = imuDataDelayed.delAng.z;
1103 q0 = stateStruct.quat[0];
1104 q1 = stateStruct.quat[1];
1105 q2 = stateStruct.quat[2];
1106 q3 = stateStruct.quat[3];
1107 dax_b = stateStruct.gyro_bias.x;
1108 day_b = stateStruct.gyro_bias.y;
1109 daz_b = stateStruct.gyro_bias.z;
1110 dvx_b = stateStruct.accel_bias.x;
1111 dvy_b = stateStruct.accel_bias.y;
1112 dvz_b = stateStruct.accel_bias.z;
1113
1114 bool quatCovResetOnly = false;
1115 if (rotVarVecPtr != nullptr) {
1116 // Handle special case where we are initialising the quaternion covariances using an earth frame
1117 // vector defining the variance of the angular alignment uncertainty. Convert he varaince vector
1118 // to a matrix and rotate into body frame. Use the exisiting gyro error propagation mechanism to
1119 // propagate the body frame angular uncertainty variances.
1120 const Vector3F &rotVarVec = *rotVarVecPtr;
1121 Matrix3F R_ef = Matrix3F (
1122 rotVarVec.x, 0.0f, 0.0f,
1123 0.0f, rotVarVec.y, 0.0f,
1124 0.0f, 0.0f, rotVarVec.z);
1125 Matrix3F Tnb;
1126 stateStruct.quat.inverse().rotation_matrix(Tnb);
1127 Matrix3F R_bf = Tnb * R_ef * Tnb.transposed();
1128 daxVar = R_bf.a.x;
1129 dayVar = R_bf.b.y;
1130 dazVar = R_bf.c.z;
1131 quatCovResetOnly = true;
1132 zeroRows(P,0,3);
1133 zeroCols(P,0,3);
1134 } else {
1135 ftype _gyrNoise = constrain_ftype(frontend->_gyrNoise, 0.0f, 1.0f);
1136 daxVar = dayVar = dazVar = sq(dt*_gyrNoise);
1137 }
1138 ftype _accNoise = badIMUdata ? BAD_IMU_DATA_ACC_P_NSE : constrain_ftype(frontend->_accNoise, 0.0f, BAD_IMU_DATA_ACC_P_NSE);
1139 dvxVar = dvyVar = dvzVar = sq(dt*_accNoise);
1140
1141 if (!inhibitDelVelBiasStates) {
1142 for (uint8_t stateIndex = 13; stateIndex <= 15; stateIndex++) {
1143 const uint8_t index = stateIndex - 13;
1144
1145 // Don't attempt learning of IMU delta velocty bias if on ground and not aligned with the gravity vector
1146 const bool is_bias_observable = (fabsF(prevTnb[index][2]) > 0.8f) || !onGround;
1147
1148 if (!is_bias_observable && !dvelBiasAxisInhibit[index]) {
1149 // store variances to be reinstated wben learning can commence later
1150 dvelBiasAxisVarPrev[index] = P[stateIndex][stateIndex];
1151 dvelBiasAxisInhibit[index] = true;
1152 } else if (is_bias_observable && dvelBiasAxisInhibit[index]) {
1153 P[stateIndex][stateIndex] = dvelBiasAxisVarPrev[index];
1154 dvelBiasAxisInhibit[index] = false;
1155 }
1156 }
1157 }
1158
1159 // calculate the predicted covariance due to inertial sensor error propagation
1160 // we calculate the lower diagonal and copy to take advantage of symmetry
1161
1162 // intermediate calculations
1163 const ftype PS0 = sq(q1);
1164 const ftype PS1 = 0.25F*daxVar;
1165 const ftype PS2 = sq(q2);
1166 const ftype PS3 = 0.25F*dayVar;
1167 const ftype PS4 = sq(q3);
1168 const ftype PS5 = 0.25F*dazVar;
1169 const ftype PS6 = 0.5F*q1;
1170 const ftype PS7 = 0.5F*q2;
1171 const ftype PS8 = PS7*P[10][11];
1172 const ftype PS9 = 0.5F*q3;
1173 const ftype PS10 = PS9*P[10][12];
1174 const ftype PS11 = 0.5F*dax - 0.5F*dax_b;

1718 for (uint8_t i=10; i<=stateIndexLim; i++) {
1719 nextP[i][i] = nextP[i][i] + processNoiseVariance[i-10];
1720 }
1721 }

1724 // interacton with other states
1725 if (!inhibitDelVelBiasStates) {
1726 for (uint8_t index=0; index<3; index++) {
1727 const uint8_t stateIndex = index + 13;
1728 if (dvelBiasAxisInhibit[index]) {
1729 zeroCols(nextP,stateIndex,stateIndex);
1730 nextP[stateIndex][stateIndex] = dvelBiasAxisVarPrev[index];
1731 }
1732 }
1733 }
1734
1735 // if the total position variance exceeds 1e4 (100m), then stop covariance
1736 // growth by setting the predicted to the previous values
1737 // This prevent an ill conditioned matrix from occurring for long periods
1738 // without GPS
1739 if ((P[7][7] + P[8][8]) > 1e4f) {
1740 for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++)
1741 {
1742 for (uint8_t j=0; j<=stateIndexLim; j++)
1743 {
1744 nextP[i][j] = P[i][j];
1745 nextP[j][i] = P[j][i];
1746 }
1747 }
1748 }
1749
1750 // covariance matrix is symmetrical, so copy diagonals and copy lower half in nextP
1751 // to lower and upper half in P
1752 for (uint8_t row = 0; row <= stateIndexLim; row++) {
1753 // copy diagonals
1754 P[row][row] = nextP[row][row];
1755 // copy off diagonals
1756 for (uint8_t column = 0 ; column < row; column++) {
1757 P[row][column] = P[column][row] = nextP[column][row];
1758 }
1759 }
1760
1761 // constrain values to prevent ill-conditioning
1762 ConstrainVariances();
1763
1764 if (vertVelVarClipCounter > 0) {
1765 vertVelVarClipCounter--;
1766 }
1767
1768 calcTiltErrorVariance();
1769
1770#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
1771 verifyTiltErrorVariance();
1772#endif
1773}

1833// force symmetry on the covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
1834void NavEKF3_core::ForceSymmetry()
1835{
1836 for (uint8_t i=1; i<=stateIndexLim; i++)
1837 {
1838 for (uint8_t j=0; j<=i-1; j++)
1839 {
1840 ftype temp = 0.5f*(P[i][j] + P[j][i]);
1841 P[i][j] = temp;
1842 P[j][i] = temp;
1843 }
1844 }
1845}
1846
1847// constrain variances (diagonal terms) in the state covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
1848// if states are inactive, zero the corresponding off-diagonals
1849void NavEKF3_core::ConstrainVariances()
1850{
1851 for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i],0.0,1.0); // attitude error
1852 for (uint8_t i=4; i<=5; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i], VEL_STATE_MIN_VARIANCE, 1.0e3); // NE velocity
1853
1854 // if vibration affected use sensor observation variances to set a floor on the state variances
1855 if (badIMUdata) {
1856 P[6][6] = fmaxF(P[6][6], sq(frontend->_gpsVertVelNoise));
1857 P[9][9] = fmaxF(P[9][9], sq(frontend->_baroAltNoise));
1858 } else if (P[6][6] < VEL_STATE_MIN_VARIANCE) {
1859 // handle collapse of the vertical velocity variance
1860 P[6][6] = VEL_STATE_MIN_VARIANCE;
1861 // this counter is decremented by 1 each prediction cycle in CovariancePrediction
1862 // resulting in the count from each clip event fading to zero over 1 second which
1863 // is sufficient to capture collapse from fusion of the lowest update rate sensor
1864 vertVelVarClipCounter += EKF_TARGET_RATE_HZ;
1865 if (vertVelVarClipCounter > VERT_VEL_VAR_CLIP_COUNT_LIM) {
1866 // reset the corresponding covariances
1867 zeroRows(P,6,6);
1868 zeroCols(P,6,6);
1869
1870 // set the variances to the measurement variance
1871 #if EK3_FEATURE_EXTERNAL_NAV
1872 if (useExtNavVel) {
1873 P[6][6] = sq(extNavVelDelayed.err);
1874 } else
1875 #endif
1876 {
1877 P[6][6] = sq(frontend->_gpsVertVelNoise);
1878 }
1879 vertVelVarClipCounter = 0;
1880 }
1881 }
1882
1883 for (uint8_t i=7; i<=9; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i], POS_STATE_MIN_VARIANCE, 1.0e6); // NED position
1884
1885 if (!inhibitDelAngBiasStates) {
1886 for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i],0.0f,sq(0.175 * dtEkfAvg));
1887 } else {
1888 zeroCols(P,10,12);
1889 zeroRows(P,10,12);
1890 }
1891
1892 const ftype minSafeStateVar = 5E-9;
1893 if (!inhibitDelVelBiasStates) {
1894
1895 // Find the maximum delta velocity bias state variance and request a covariance reset if any variance is below the safe minimum
1896 ftype maxStateVar = 0.0F;
1897 bool resetRequired = false;
1898 for (uint8_t stateIndex=13; stateIndex<=15; stateIndex++) {
1899 if (P[stateIndex][stateIndex] > maxStateVar) {
1900 maxStateVar = P[stateIndex][stateIndex];
1901 } else if (P[stateIndex][stateIndex] < minSafeStateVar) {
1902 resetRequired = true;
1903 }
1904 }
1905
1906 // To ensure stability of the covariance matrix operations, the ratio of a max and min variance must
1907 // not exceed 100 and the minimum variance must not fall below the target minimum
1908 ftype minAllowedStateVar = fmaxF(0.01f * maxStateVar, minSafeStateVar);
1909 for (uint8_t stateIndex=13; stateIndex<=15; stateIndex++) {
1910 P[stateIndex][stateIndex] = constrain_ftype(P[stateIndex][stateIndex], minAllowedStateVar, sq(10.0f * dtEkfAvg));
1911 }
1912
1913 // If any one axis has fallen below the safe minimum, all delta velocity covariance terms must be reset to zero
1914 if (resetRequired) {
1915 // reset all delta velocity bias covariances
1916 zeroCols(P,13,15);
1917 zeroRows(P,13,15);
1918 // set all delta velocity bias variances to initial values and zero bias states
1919 P[13][13] = sq(ACCEL_BIAS_LIM_SCALER * frontend->_accBiasLim * dtEkfAvg);
1920 P[14][14] = P[13][13];
1921 P[15][15] = P[13][13];
1922 stateStruct.accel_bias.zero();
1923 }
1924
1925 } else {
1926 zeroCols(P,13,15);
1927 zeroRows(P,13,15);
1928 // set all delta velocity bias variances to a margin above the minimum safe value
1929 for (uint8_t i=0; i<=2; i++) {
1930 const uint8_t stateIndex = i + 13;
1931 P[stateIndex][stateIndex] = fmaxF(P[stateIndex][stateIndex], minSafeStateVar * 10.0F);
1932 }
1933 }
1934
1935 if (!inhibitMagStates) {
1936 for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i],0.0f,0.01f); // earth magnetic field
1937 for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i],0.0f,0.01f); // body magnetic field
1938 } else {
1939 zeroCols(P,16,21);
1940 zeroRows(P,16,21);
1941 }
1942
1943 if (!inhibitWindStates) {
1944 for (uint8_t i=22; i<=23; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_ftype(P[i][i],0.0f,WIND_VEL_VARIANCE_MAX);
1945 } else {
1946 zeroCols(P,22,23);
1947 zeroRows(P,22,23);
1948 }
1949}

1951// constrain states using WMM tables and specified limit
1952void NavEKF3_core::MagTableConstrain(void)
1953{
1954 // constrain to error from table earth field
1955 ftype limit_ga = frontend->_mag_ef_limit * 0.001f;
1956 stateStruct.earth_magfield.x = constrain_ftype(stateStruct.earth_magfield.x,
1957 table_earth_field_ga.x-limit_ga,
1958 table_earth_field_ga.x+limit_ga);
1959 stateStruct.earth_magfield.y = constrain_ftype(stateStruct.earth_magfield.y,
1960 table_earth_field_ga.y-limit_ga,
1961 table_earth_field_ga.y+limit_ga);
1962 stateStruct.earth_magfield.z = constrain_ftype(stateStruct.earth_magfield.z,
1963 table_earth_field_ga.z-limit_ga,
1964 table_earth_field_ga.z+limit_ga);
1965}

1967// constrain states to prevent ill-conditioning
1968void NavEKF3_core::ConstrainStates()
1969{
1970 // quaternions are limited between +-1
1971 for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
1972 // velocity limit 500 m/sec (could set this based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS)
1973 for (uint8_t i=4; i<=6; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-5.0e2f,5.0e2f);
1974 // position limit TODO apply circular limit
1975 for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-EK3_POSXY_STATE_LIMIT,EK3_POSXY_STATE_LIMIT);
1976 // height limit covers home alt on everest through to home alt at SL and balloon drop
1977 stateStruct.position.z = constrain_ftype(stateStruct.position.z,-4.0e4f,1.0e4f);
1978 // gyro bias limit (this needs to be set based on manufacturers specs)
1979 for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-GYRO_BIAS_LIMIT*dtEkfAvg,GYRO_BIAS_LIMIT*dtEkfAvg);
1980 // the accelerometer bias limit is controlled by a user adjustable parameter
1981 for (uint8_t i=13; i<=15; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-frontend->_accBiasLim*dtEkfAvg,frontend->_accBiasLim*dtEkfAvg);
1982 // earth magnetic field limit
1983 if (frontend->_mag_ef_limit <= 0 || !have_table_earth_field) {
1984 // constrain to +/-1Ga
1985 for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
1986 } else {
1987 // use table constrain
1988 MagTableConstrain();
1989 }
1990 // body magnetic field limit
1991 for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-0.5f,0.5f);
1992 // wind velocity limit 100 m/s (could be based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS) - TODO apply circular limit
1993 for (uint8_t i=22; i<=23; i++) statesArray[i] = constrain_ftype(statesArray[i],-100.0f,100.0f);
1994 // constrain the terrain state to be below the vehicle height unless we are using terrain as the height datum
1995 if (!inhibitGndState) {
1996 terrainState = MAX(terrainState, stateStruct.position.z + rngOnGnd);
1997 }
1998}

2000// calculate the NED earth spin vector in rad/sec
2001void NavEKF3_core::calcEarthRateNED(Vector3F &omega, int32_t latitude) const
2002{
2003 ftype lat_rad = radians(latitude*1.0e-7f);
2004 omega.x = earthRate*cosF(lat_rad);
2005 omega.y = 0;
2006 omega.z = -earthRate*sinF(lat_rad);

2009// set yaw from a single magnetometer sample
2010void NavEKF3_core::setYawFromMag()
2011{
2012 if (!use_compass()) {
2013 return;
2014 }
2015
2016 // read the magnetometer data
2017 readMagData();
2018
2019 // use best of either 312 or 321 rotation sequence when calculating yaw
2020 rotationOrder order;
2021 bestRotationOrder(order);
2022 Vector3F eulerAngles;
2023 Matrix3F Tbn_zeroYaw;
2024 if (order == rotationOrder::TAIT_BRYAN_321) {
2025 // rolled more than pitched so use 321 rotation order
2026 stateStruct.quat.to_euler(eulerAngles);
2027 Tbn_zeroYaw.from_euler(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y, 0.0f);
2028 } else if (order == rotationOrder::TAIT_BRYAN_312) {
2029 // pitched more than rolled so use 312 rotation order
2030 eulerAngles = stateStruct.quat.to_vector312();
2031 Tbn_zeroYaw.from_euler312(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y, 0.0f);
2032 } else {
2033 // rotation order not supported
2034 return;
2035 }
2036
2037 Vector3F magMeasNED = Tbn_zeroYaw * magDataDelayed.mag;
2038 ftype yawAngMeasured = wrap_PI(-atan2F(magMeasNED.y, magMeasNED.x) + MagDeclination());
2039
2040 // update quaternion states and covariances
2041 resetQuatStateYawOnly(yawAngMeasured, sq(MAX(frontend->_yawNoise, 1.0e-2f)), order);
2042}

2044// update mag field states and associated variances using magnetomer and declination data
2045void NavEKF3_core::resetMagFieldStates()
2046{
2047 // Rotate Mag measurements into NED to set initial NED magnetic field states
2048
2049 // update rotation matrix from body to NED frame
2050 stateStruct.quat.inverse().rotation_matrix(prevTnb);
2051
2052 if (have_table_earth_field && frontend->_mag_ef_limit > 0) {
2053 stateStruct.earth_magfield = table_earth_field_ga;
2054 } else {
2055 stateStruct.earth_magfield = prevTnb.transposed() * magDataDelayed.mag;
2056 }
2057
2058 // set the NE earth magnetic field states using the published declination
2059 // and set the corresponding variances and covariances
2060 alignMagStateDeclination();
2061
2062 // set the remaining variances and covariances
2063 zeroRows(P,18,21);
2064 zeroCols(P,18,21);
2065 P[18][18] = sq(frontend->_magNoise);
2066 P[19][19] = P[18][18];
2067 P[20][20] = P[18][18];
2068 P[21][21] = P[18][18];
2069
2070 // record the fact we have initialised the magnetic field states
2071 recordMagReset();
2072}

2082 zeroRows(P,0,3);

2088// calculate the tilt error variance
2089void NavEKF3_core::calcTiltErrorVariance()
2090{
2091 const ftype &q0 = stateStruct.quat[0];
2092 const ftype &q1 = stateStruct.quat[1];
2093 const ftype &q2 = stateStruct.quat[2];
2094 const ftype &q3 = stateStruct.quat[3];
2095
2096 // equations generated by quaternion_error_propagation(): in AP_NavEKF3/derivation/main.py
2097 // only diagonals have been used
2098 // dq0 ... dq3 terms have been zeroed
2099 const ftype PS1 = q0*q1 + q2*q3;
2100 const ftype PS2 = q1*PS1;
2101 const ftype PS4 = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
2102 const ftype PS5 = q0*PS4;
2103 const ftype PS6 = 2*PS2 + PS5;
2104 const ftype PS8 = PS1*q2;
2105 const ftype PS10 = PS4*q3;
2106 const ftype PS11 = PS10 + 2*PS8;
2107 const ftype PS12 = PS1*q3;
2108 const ftype PS13 = PS4*q2;
2109 const ftype PS14 = -2*PS12 + PS13;
2110 const ftype PS15 = PS1*q0;
2111 const ftype PS16 = q1*PS4;
2112 const ftype PS17 = 2*PS15 - PS16;
2113 const ftype PS18 = q0*q2 - q1*q3;
2114 const ftype PS19 = PS18*q2;
2115 const ftype PS20 = 2*PS19 + PS5;
2116 const ftype PS22 = q1*PS18;
2117 const ftype PS23 = -PS10 + 2*PS22;
2118 const ftype PS25 = PS18*q3;
2119 const ftype PS26 = PS16 + 2*PS25;
2120 const ftype PS28 = PS18*q0;
2121 const ftype PS29 = -PS13 + 2*PS28;
2122 const ftype PS32 = PS12 + PS28;
2123 const ftype PS33 = PS19 + PS2;
2124 const ftype PS34 = PS15 - PS25;
2125 const ftype PS35 = PS22 - PS8;
2126
2127 tiltErrorVariance = 4*sq(PS11)*P[2][2] + 4*sq(PS14)*P[3][3] + 4*sq(PS17)*P[0][0] + 4*sq(PS6)*P[1][1];
2128 tiltErrorVariance += 4*sq(PS20)*P[2][2] + 4*sq(PS23)*P[1][1] + 4*sq(PS26)*P[3][3] + 4*sq(PS29)*P[0][0];
2129 tiltErrorVariance += 16*sq(PS32)*P[1][1] + 16*sq(PS33)*P[3][3] + 16*sq(PS34)*P[2][2] + 16*sq(PS35)*P[0][0];
2130
2131 tiltErrorVariance = constrain_ftype(tiltErrorVariance, 0.0f, sq(radians(30.0f)));
2132}

2134void NavEKF3_core::bestRotationOrder(rotationOrder &order)
2135{
2136 if (fabsF(prevTnb[2][0]) < fabsF(prevTnb[2][1])) {
2137 // rolled more than pitched so use 321 sequence
2138 order = rotationOrder::TAIT_BRYAN_321;
2139 } else {
2140 // pitched more than rolled so use 312 sequence
2141 order = rotationOrder::TAIT_BRYAN_312;
2142 }
2143}

2146// calculate the tilt error variance using an alternative numerical difference technique
2147// and log with value generated by NavEKF3_core::calcTiltErrorVariance()
2148void NavEKF3_core::verifyTiltErrorVariance()
2149{
2150 const Vector3f gravity_ef = Vector3f(0.0f,0.0f,1.0f);
2151 Matrix3f Tnb;
2152 const float quat_delta = 0.001f;
2153 float tiltErrorVarianceAlt = 0.0f;
2154 for (uint8_t index = 0; index<4; index++) {
2155 QuaternionF quat = stateStruct.quat;
2156
2157 // Add a positive increment to the quaternion element and calculate the tilt error vector
2158 quat[index] = stateStruct.quat[index] + quat_delta;
2159 quat.inverse().rotation_matrix(Tnb);
2160 const Vector3f gravity_bf_plus = Tnb * gravity_ef;
2161
2162 // Add a negative increment to the quaternion element and calculate the tilt error vector
2163 quat[index] = stateStruct.quat[index] - quat_delta;
2164 quat.inverse().rotation_matrix(Tnb);
2165 const Vector3f gravity_bf_minus = Tnb * gravity_ef;
2166
2167 // calculate the angular difference between the two vectors using a small angle assumption
2168 const Vector3f tilt_diff_vec = gravity_bf_minus % gravity_bf_plus;
2169
2170 // calculate the partial derivative of angle error wrt the quaternion element
2171 const float tilt_error_derivative = tilt_diff_vec.length() / (2.0f * quat_delta);
2172
2173 // sum the contribution of the quaternion elemnent variance to the tilt angle error variance
2174 tiltErrorVarianceAlt += P[index][index] * sq(tilt_error_derivative);
2175 }
2176
2177 tiltErrorVarianceAlt = MIN(tiltErrorVarianceAlt, sq(radians(30.0f)));
2178 if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastLogTime_ms > 500) {
2179 lastLogTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2180 const struct log_XKTV msg {
2181 LOG_PACKET_HEADER_INIT(LOG_XKTV_MSG),
2182 time_us : dal.micros64(),
2183 core : core_index,
2184 tvs : float(tiltErrorVariance),
2185 tvd : float(tiltErrorVarianceAlt),
2186 };
2187 AP::logger().WriteBlock(&msg, sizeof(msg));
2188 }
2189}
2190#endif

2192/*
2193 move the EKF origin to the current position at 1Hz. The public_origin doesn't move.
2194 By moving the EKF origin we keep the distortion due to spherical
2195 shape of the earth to a minimum.
2196 */
2197void NavEKF3_core::moveEKFOrigin(void)
2198{
2199 // only move origin when we have a origin and we're using GPS
2200 if (!frontend->common_origin_valid || !filterStatus.flags.using_gps) {
2201 return;
2202 }
2203
2204 // move the origin to the current state location
2205 Location loc = EKF_origin;
2206 loc.offset(stateStruct.position.x, stateStruct.position.y);
2207 const Vector2F diffNE = loc.get_distance_NE_ftype(EKF_origin);
2208 EKF_origin = loc;
2209
2210 // now fix all output states
2211 stateStruct.position.xy() += diffNE;
2212 outputDataNew.position.xy() += diffNE;
2213 outputDataDelayed.position.xy() += diffNE;
2214
2215 for (unsigned index=0; index < imu_buffer_length; index++) {
2216 storedOutput[index].position.xy() += diffNE;
2217 }
2218}
